# angular routing and navigation
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tUCa3JcFILI
Steps:
- Configure the routes
RouterModule.forRoot([
{
  path: '/',
  component: HomeComponent
},
{
  path: '/users/:id',
  component: UserComponent
},
{
  path: '**',
  component: ErrorComponent
}
])
- Add a router outlet
- Router Link
<a routerLink="/users"> -- simple routes, string values
<a [routerLink]="['users',user.id]"> -- property binding is used for parameters
- Active Links
<li routerLinkActive="active current"><a routerLink="/somepath">somepath</a></li>
<li routerLinkActive="active current"><a routerLink="/somepath2">somepath2</a></li>
- Accessing route parameters
(/users/:id)
Inside component class constructor:
Construcor(private route: ActivatedRoute){}
this.route.paramMap.subscribe(params=>{
  console.log(params);
  let id = +params.get('id');
  // service.getProfile(id);
  console.log(id);
});
